items.title: Harvey Weinstein's rape retrial begins in New York
items.description: Weinstein, who has pleaded not guilty to sex crimes, returns to court after a conviction was overturned.

items.title: Trump accuses Zelensky of harming Ukraine peace negotiations
items.description: The comments came after Kyiv rejected suggestions it could recognise Russian control of Crimea.

items.title: Opportunity for big US-China trade deal, says Bessent
items.description: The comments from the US Treasury Secretary come as the trade war between the world's two biggest economies has escalated.

items.title: India closes main border crossing with Pakistan after Kashmir attack
items.description: Visas held by some Pakistanis are also cancelled after gunmen killed tourists in Indian-administered Kashmir.

items.title: Abbas calls Hamas 'sons of dogs' and demands release of Gaza hostages
items.description: Palestinian Authority president says that Hamas has given Israel "excuses" to continue the Gaza war.
